AMD shipped the first consumer 64-bit chip in 2003. Ten years later, the majority of gamers – 53.96 per cent – have 4GB of RAM or less. This is the case despite the fact that more than 75 per cent of all users are running 64-bit operating systems. Only 13.22 per cent of gamers, according to the Steam Hardware Survey, are running Windows 7 32-bit, and that’s the most popular 32-bit OS.
